cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.HC 

The paper deals with the problem of estimating body mass index (BMI) category from facial images, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as ordinal regression and Siamese architectures, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of facial images also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed method in healthcare, which could also make it relevant to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category.
